[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":334},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F10\u002Fsetting-up-routes-in-nuxt\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F10\u002Fsetting-up-routes-in-nuxt\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F10\u002Fsetting-up-routes-in-nuxt\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F10\u002Fsetting-up-routes-in-nuxt\u002F":311,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F10\u002Fsetting-up-routes-in-nuxt\u002F":319},"\u002Fvue\u002F20190810\u002F3385236004\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":295,"date":296,"description":19,"extension":297,"lang":298,"meta":299,"navigation":300,"path":301,"readingMinutes":302,"seo":303,"standalone":304,"stem":305,"tags":306,"tldr":308,"updated":296,"url":309,"__hash__":310},"content\u002Fen\u002FVue\u002Fsetting-up-routes-in-nuxt.md","Setting Up Routes in Nuxt","3360530428",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":284},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,34,38,46,53,59,70,75,81,86,92,98,101,105,123,129,136,141,147,153,156,160,167,172,175,202,207,213,218,224,229,241,246,253,257,271,275],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Nuxt generates routes differently from how you'd usually do it. Here's a quick walkthrough on what it actually does.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"starting-out","Starting out",[17,25,26],{},"Before walking through the routing, let's spin up a Nuxt project. If you haven't done that before, see my earlier post:",[17,28,29],{},[30,31,33],"a",{"href":32},"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F09\u002Fcreate-a-nuxtjs-project\u002F","Setting Up a Nuxt.js Project",[12,35,37],{"id":36},"routes","Routes",[17,39,40,41,45],{},"In Vue CLI, you configure routes in ",[42,43,44],"code",{},"router.js"," like this:",[17,47,48],{},[49,50],"img",{"alt":51,"src":52},"Example from RagnarokShopV3","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FdIQq0I5.png",[17,54,55,56,58],{},"But Nuxt is different — the router is auto-generated, you don't touch ",[42,57,44],{}," at all. Let's see this in action.",[17,60,61,62,65,66,69],{},"When you run ",[42,63,64],{},"npm run dev",", Nuxt creates a ",[42,67,68],{},".nuxt"," folder.",[17,71,72],{},[49,73],{"alt":68,"src":74},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FGyVnFv9.png",[17,76,77,78,80],{},"Inside it you'll find a ",[42,79,44],{},".",[17,82,83],{},[49,84],{"alt":44,"src":85},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FUUISimR.png",[17,87,88,89,91],{},"Open ",[42,90,44],{}," and scroll to the bottom — you'll see the auto-generated routes (ignore the red squigglies).",[17,93,94],{},[49,95],{"alt":96,"src":97},"auto-generated","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FLKbqygn.png",[17,99,100],{},"So how does it actually work?",[12,102,104],{"id":103},"how-its-generated","How it's generated",[17,106,107,108,111,112,115,116,118,119,122],{},"Nuxt reads the ",[42,109,110],{},".vue"," files under ",[42,113,114],{},"pages\u002F",". Right now ",[42,117,114],{}," only contains ",[42,120,121],{},"index.vue",", so Nuxt generates one route.",[17,124,125],{},[49,126],{"alt":127,"src":128},"router","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FcrXTiD0.png",[17,130,131,132,135],{},"Knowing that, let's create a ",[42,133,134],{},"pages.vue"," underneath and see what happens.",[17,137,138],{},[49,139],{"alt":134,"src":140},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F63ZDVFX.png",[17,142,88,143,146],{},[42,144,145],{},"\u002F.nuxt\u002Frouter.js"," again to see what changed.",[17,148,149],{},[49,150],{"alt":151,"src":152},"Image","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FcF94XEB.png",[17,154,155],{},"It auto-generated the route for you — pretty magical, right?",[12,157,159],{"id":158},"nested-routes","Nested routes",[17,161,162,163,166],{},"Nested routes are a really common pattern. With Vue Router we use ",[42,164,165],{},"children"," to declare nesting:",[17,168,169],{},[49,170],{"alt":51,"src":171},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FkJUx9rO.png",[17,173,174],{},"How do you do nested routes in Nuxt? Manually? Nope — Nuxt strongly prefers auto-generation. Manual config is painful in Nuxt.",[17,176,177,178,181,182,184,185,188,189,191,192,194,195,197,198,188,200,80],{},"Say I want a nested router under ",[42,179,180],{},"pages"," with ",[42,183,121],{}," (the main page), ",[42,186,187],{},"about.vue",", and ",[42,190,134],{},". Here's how — create a folder named ",[42,193,180],{}," underneath, and inside it create ",[42,196,121],{},", ",[42,199,187],{},[42,201,134],{},[17,203,204],{},[49,205],{"alt":180,"src":206},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FILIQTCQ.png",[17,208,209,210,212],{},"Now check ",[42,211,145],{},":",[17,214,215],{},[49,216],{"alt":44,"src":217},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fwb2op5C.png",[17,219,220,221,223],{},"The nested router gets created. One thing to watch — at the parent level there's also a ",[42,222,134],{}," with the same name as the folder.",[17,225,226],{},[49,227],{"alt":134,"src":228},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FTltnxKn.png",[17,230,231,232,234,235,237,238,240],{},"The folder name has to match the sibling ",[42,233,134],{},", otherwise things break. For example, if I delete the top-level ",[42,236,134],{},", here's what ",[42,239,145],{}," becomes:",[17,242,243],{},[49,244],{"alt":44,"src":245},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FCtIg5IL.png",[17,247,248,249,252],{},"It's no longer a nested route. So remember — to create nested routes, you need a same-named ",[42,250,251],{},"XXX.vue"," sitting next to the folder.",[12,254,256],{"id":255},"wrap-up","Wrap-up",[17,258,259,260,263,264,267,268,80],{},"One last note — in Nuxt, the recommended way to switch routes is ",[42,261,262],{},"\u003Cnuxt-link to=\"\u002F\">Home\u003C\u002Fnuxt-link>",". If you use the named-route form ",[42,265,266],{},"\u003Cnuxt-link to=\"{name: 'xxx'}\">Home\u003C\u002Fnuxt-link>",", make sure to include the nested folder in the name. For the example above, that's ",[42,269,270],{},"\u003Cnuxt-link to=\"{name: 'pages-about'}\">Home\u003C\u002Fnuxt-link>",[12,272,274],{"id":273},"references","References",[17,276,277,283],{},[30,278,282],{"href":279,"rel":280},"https:\u002F\u002Fzh.nuxtjs.org\u002Fguide\u002Frouting\u002F",[281],"nofollow","Basic Routing"," (article in Mandarin)",{"title":285,"searchDepth":286,"depth":286,"links":287},"",2,[288,289,290,291,292,293,294],{"id":14,"depth":286,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":286,"text":23},{"id":36,"depth":286,"text":37},{"id":103,"depth":286,"text":104},{"id":158,"depth":286,"text":159},{"id":255,"depth":286,"text":256},{"id":273,"depth":286,"text":274},"Vue","2019-08-10 22:29:02","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002Fsetting-up-routes-in-nuxt","2",{"title":6,"description":19},false,"en\u002FVue\u002Fsetting-up-routes-in-nuxt",[295,307],"Nuxt",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F10\u002Fsetting-up-routes-in-nuxt\u002F","RoXtz_O2XzNzSwyXz_Tzs2a6d_b6MBx0FgDh61urvzY",{"newer":312,"older":316},{"url":313,"title":314,"date":315},"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F16\u002Fnuxtjs-navigation-guards\u002F","Nuxt.js Navigation Guards","2019-08-16 13:01:13",{"url":32,"title":317,"date":318},"Creating a NuxtJS Project","2019-08-09 15:49:13",[320,325,329],{"url":321,"title":322,"date":323,"readingMinutes":324},"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2025\u002F12\u002F04\u002Fvue-nuxt-project-folder-structure\u002F","Vue\u002FNuxt Project Architecture: How to Pick the Right Folder Structure for Your Team","2025-12-04 11:40:56","7",{"url":326,"title":327,"date":328,"readingMinutes":324},"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2025\u002F11\u002F06\u002Fvue-sfc-spec-block-for-ai-development\u002F","Use a Custom &lt;spec lang=\"md\"&gt; Block in Vue SFC for Smoother AI Development","2025-11-06 13:45:34",{"url":330,"title":331,"date":332,"readingMinutes":333},"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2025\u002F02\u002F16\u002Fvue3-shallowref-vs-ref\u002F","shallowRef: Another Way to Declare Reactivity Besides ref","2025-02-16 19:32:58","4",1784020383601]